Qualifications:
1. Possess a Bachelor’s degree from an accredited college or university with a major in Business, Hospitality, Recreation, Communication, Management or a related field; AND Have had at least one (1) year of full-time work experience in the management of a park or recreation facility or in the management of a business that provides services to customers;
2. Possess an Associate’s degree or equivalent education from an accredited college or university with a major in Business, Hospitality, Recreation, Communication, Management or a related field; AND Have at least three (3) years of full-time work experience in the management of a park or recreation facility, or in the management of a business that provides services to customers;
3. Must be a high school graduate or have a certificate of successful completion of the General Education Development (GED) Test; AND Have at least five (5) years of full-time work experience in the management of a park or recreation facility, or in the management of a business that provides services to customers.
4. Possess a valid motor vehicle operator’s or chauffeur’s license.
5. Must maintain a valid motor vehicle operator’s or chauffeur’s license.

1. Requires a B.A. or B.S degree;
2. with a minimum of 1 year of experience;
3. or any combination of education and experience, which would provide an equivalent background.
